reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: As a self-proclaimed connoisseur of comfortable sleeping arrangements, I can confidently say that the VECELO Queen Size Upholstered Bed Frame exceeded my expectations. From its plush velvet upholstery to its adjustable headboard, this bed frame is a luxurious addition to any bedroom.The dark grey velvet adds a touch of elegance to the room, instantly elevating its aesthetic appeal. But it's not just about looks; the sturdy wood slat support provides exceptional stability, ensuring a peaceful night's sleep without the need for a box spring.One of the standout features for me is the adjustable headboard, which allows for customizable comfort while reading or watching TV in bed. It's a small detail that makes a big difference in overall relaxation.Setting up this bed frame was a breeze, thanks to clear instructions and minimal assembly required. Within no time, I had transformed my bedroom into a sanctuary of comfort and style.Overall, I highly recommend the VECELO Queen Size Upholstered Bed Frame to anyone in search of a blend of comfort, style, and durability. It's the perfect foundation for a restful night's sleep and a stylish bedroom retreat.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy, pretty, and easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: For the price, this is a great frame. It was much easier to put together than I had anticipated, it came with all of the tools needed however the slats might need bolted down—they’re just attached with Velcro which would be fine if the bed weren’t for a naughty 3 year old boy (I can see the slats becoming a baseball bat). They’re made of wood, as is the support it rests on so it wouldn’t be hard to make a more permanent attachment. The fabric is beautiful, we chose the blue one, it’s soft and velvetty and a beautiful vibrant color. It’s quite sturdy and strong, I’m impressed because I expected it to be a little less strong for $99. We love it! My son is upgrading from a rickety old metal bed frame that squeaked and rattled and swung around when you sat down on it, screws falling out and ready for retirement. We’re pleased with this purchase. One thing I would say it measure your mattress and make sure it will fit, ours is fine but it was a tight squeeze. I’ll post a picture later
